# ── Supabase (required for auth) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Create a free Supabase project at supabase.com. Get these from:
# Settings → API → Project URL and Anon Key (public, safe to expose)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ── Ghost journal (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Point these at any Ghost blog and the Field Journal section switches from
# the local entries in src/data/journal.ts to live posts.
# Content API keys are read-only and safe to expose in a static site.
# Ghost admin → Settings → Integrations → Add custom integration → Content API key
#VITE_GHOST_URL=https://zink.ghost.io
#VITE_GHOST_KEY=22444f78447824223cefc48062
#VITE_GHOST_TAG=journal

# ── PathCompanion live sync (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# PathCompanion is a PlayFab-backed app. Set its PlayFab Title ID and the
# deployed site logs into PlayFab in the browser and re-reads the character's
# Public UserData on every visit — the footer badge flips to "live". The Title
# ID is public (it rides every PlayFab request). Find it in DevTools → Network
# while viewing the sheet: the LoginWithCustomID / GetUserData calls go to
# https://<TitleId>.playfabapi.com/Client/...
#VITE_PC_PLAYFAB_TITLE=XXXXX

# Legacy fallback: a plain GET endpoint returning character JSON, if you have
# one. {key} {account} {character} are substituted.
#VITE_PC_API=https://host/character?key={key}

# Override the baked-in character key without touching code:
#PATHCOMPANION_KEY=eyJhY2NvdW50IjoiMjdDN0IzRjY0RkQ4NTU5MiIsImNoYXJhY3RlciI6ImNoYXJhY3RlcjEzIn0=
